# Sync local `main` with merged PRs

## Why

Forgotten `git pull` on `main` causes confusing drift vs GitHub after PR merges.

## Automation (authoritative)

This repo ships `githooks/post-checkout`. After a **one-time** setup per clone:

`git config core.hooksPath githooks`

…every `git switch main` / `git checkout main` runs `git pull --ff-only origin main` (quiet). If you are offline or `main` diverged, the hook prints a short message instead of merging blindly.

## Agent reminder

When work assumes **current `main`** (release hygiene, branching from main, “is this bug on main?”, CI parity):

1. Confirm branch is `main` (or explicitly note otherwise).
2. Run `git pull --ff-only origin main` (or `git fetch origin main && git merge --ff-only origin/main`) before conclusions that depend on upstream state.

This does **not** replace fetching other branches or rebasing feature work; it only guards **local main vs origin/main**.
